abstract.value: Dr. Frank Hentschker is a faculty member in the Theatre program at The Graduate Center, City University of New York, and serves as the Executive Director and Director of Programs at the Martin E. Segal Theatre Center. The collection contains Off and Off-Off Broadway ephemera Hentschker collected, including fliers, invitations, and programs. Materials date from 2004 to 2009.

p.value: Identification of item, date; Frank Hentschker Collection of Off and Off-Off Broadway Ephemera; MSS 416; box number; folder number; Fales Library and Special Collections, New York University.
Donated by Frank Hentschker in 2006. The accession number associated with this gift is 2014.416.

Dr. Frank Hentschker holds a Ph.D. in Theatre from the Theatre Institute in Giessen, Germany and joined the Faculty of the Ph.D. Program in Theatre at The Graduate Center, City University of New York, in 2009. Frank Hentschker is the Executive Director and Director of Programs at the Martin E. Segal Theatre Center at the CUNY Graduate Center. Through his work at the Segal Theatre Center, Hentschker founded the annual festival <emph render="italic">Prelude: At the Forefront of Contemporary NYC Theatre</emph> and<emph render="italic">PEN: World Voices Playwrights Series</emph>. Before working at CUNY, Hentschker worked as a producer, consultant, and actor, in the U.S. and Europe.
The collection contains Off and Off-Off Broadway ephemera collected by Frank Hentschker. Materials include fliers, invitations, and programs. The materials date from 2004 to 2009.
